      <p>Birth: Edinburgh, Scotland (21 July 1766)</p>
      <p>Death: Edinburgh (13 June 1844)</p>
      
      <p>Research Field: Chemistry</p>
      <p>Education: MD (1787, Edinburgh)</p>
      <p>Career: Professor of Chemistry, Glasgow (1787); resigned upon appointment as Assistant Professor of Medicine, Glasgow (1789); Joint Professor of Chemistry, Edinburgh, with Joseph Black (1795); sole Professor of Chemistry upon Black's death (1799); discovered strontium (1791/2); resigned professorship (1843)</p>
      
